Chrome Guard

Chrome Guard is a lightweight desktop helper that launches Google Chrome using a dedicated low-latency profile and monitors how the browser uses system resources. It shows real-time CPU usage, identifies which Chrome process is causing load, and estimates per-tab activity using the Chrome DevTools Protocol. A simple Tkinter interface lets you enter a URL and launch Chrome directly from the app.

Features

• Launch Chrome with performance-optimized flags
• Monitor total Chrome CPU usage
• Identify the highest-CPU Chrome process (tab renderer, extension process, GPU process, utility process, etc.)
• Display estimated per-tab CPU contribution
• Show live meters for Chrome CPU usage
• Log alerts when Chrome processes create sustained load
• Provide a one-window desktop UI for launching and observing Chrome

