Installation

Create a virtual environment
python3 -m venv .venv

Activate it
source .venv/bin/activate

Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

Running the App

To start the UI:
python3 scripts/run_gui.py

This opens the Chrome Guard window where you can type a URL and monitor Chrome’s activity in real time.

To run the monitor without the UI:
python3 scripts/run_monitor_only.py

This prints Chrome CPU statistics in the terminal.

Configuration

You can override defaults using environment variables such as:

CHROME_GUARD_CHROME_PATH
CHROME_GUARD_CPU_TOTAL
CHROME_GUARD_CPU_SINGLE
CHROME_GUARD_POLL_INTERVAL
CHROME_GUARD_SUSTAINED_HITS

Default values are defined in config.py.
